Lower the hurdle of not knowing.
When you guess and pretend to know what you don't know, the hurdle of "I don't know" rises, and you start acting like a "know-it-all" by guessing things you don't know with low guess accuracy. We must lower the hurdle by expressing our ignorance on a regular basis.

